        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Providence</placeName>
                <date>Sunday</date> Morning</p>
            <p><date>November 30, 1859</date>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Mr Editor</p>
            <p>Knowing that you are interested<lb/> in the welfare of the <sic>hebrew</sic>
                congregations through<lb/>out the <placeName>United States</placeName>, and
                    <sic>allways</sic><lb/> ready, to insert in your valuable<lb/> Paper all facts
                concerning our<lb/> holy Religion, I take pleasure<lb/> of informing you of the following<lb/>
                <del>facts</del> About two years ago <persName>Mr<lb/> A. Wormser</persName>
                <sic>than</sic> a resident of<lb/> this city, has at that time remo<lb/>ved with his
                family to <placeName>New York</placeName>,<lb/> and from that city left for
                        <placeName>Uropa<add>?</add></placeName><lb/> to <del>get</del> see those
                that where dear<lb/> to him, and on saying good <sic>by</sic><lb/> to his Brethren
                of the congregation<lb/> San<add>?</add> of Israel <sic>hi</sic> promised, if<lb/>
                his life was spared to return in<lb/>
                <sic>safty</sic> to this country, <sic>hi</sic> would</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>give as a donation to the Syna<lb/>goge a Favor, his promise is<lb/>
                <sic>fullfilled</sic> for on <date>Sunday the 27<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date> inst<lb/>
                <del>and by previous writing</del><lb/>
                <sic>hi</sic> presented to ex President <persName>Mr<lb/> B. Shuman</persName> in
                the <sic>Synagoge</sic> a<lb/> handsome favor <persName>Mr Wormser</persName><lb/>
                addressed the President very fluently<lb/> the President <sic>than</sic> thanked
                    <persName>Mr Wormser</persName><lb/> in <sic>behalve</sic> of the members of
                the<lb/> congregation Sons of Israel,<lb/> and accepted that valuable gift<lb/> and
                as <sic>hi</sic> addressed <persName>Mr Wormser</persName>,<lb/> all eyes
                    <sic>where</sic> full of tears, and<lb/> all felt that such a gift must<lb/> be
                    <sic>recordet</sic> above, in the great<lb/> Book of Life, after the
                ceremonies<lb/> the President called a meeting and<lb/> it was unanimously
                resolved<lb/> that <persName>Mr A Wormser</persName> be elected<lb/> a
                    <sic>honerary</sic> member. It was then<lb/> moved and carried <persName>Mr
                    Wormsers</persName><lb/> name be <sic>instered</sic> on the regular</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>List, and that his Name may be<lb/> mentioned at each prayer the<lb/> meeting
                    <sic>than</sic> adjourned, and<lb/> the President invited the Ladies<lb/> and
                Gentlemen to the honor<lb/> of <persName>Mr Joseph Stern</persName> to a<lb/> repast
                prepared for this ocas<lb/>sion, ample justice was done<lb/> to all eatables, and
                the company<lb/> brook<add>?</add> up much pleased.</p>
            <p>Mr Editor</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">You please insert the<lb/> above as an editorial and<lb/> send your
                Bill for payment.</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Yours</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">A Goldsmith</persName> Sec.</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">Per B D</p>
        </body>
